OL,6,FAmy said: "I think they could tell we
OL,7,Fwere the kids in care coming into the
OL,8,Fcity by ourselves - we were more
OL,9,Fvulnerable. Nobody's at home waiting
OL,10,Ffor us.
OL,12,F"The men who were actually grooming me
OL,13,Fwere the only ones who asked, "How are
OL,14,Fyou doing?" You feel they're caring
OL,15,Ffor you, you don't realise you're
OL,16,Fbeing groomed."
OL,18,FSarah says it was also in Glasgow's
OL,19,Fcity centre that she was first
OL,20,Fintroduced to the gang.
